                      Nature stories                    Gaia, or Mother Earth, was the oldest of the gods of the early Greeks. She was born from Chaos, the great void of emptiness within the universe. Gaia is mother to the sea and the sky, the mountains, plains and rivers that make up the earth. She is the promordial element from which all gods originated, and was worshipped throughout Greece by humans and gods alike. Welcoming the advent of spring, Gaia, the ongoing exhibition of paintings and sculptures by 30 artists, is a joyful and colourful celebration of Nature. Participating artists include Anita Gurbaxani, B.R. Panesar, Biswarup Garai, Dhiren Sasmal, Malay Chandan Saha, Rajib Bhattacharjee (a painting by him appears above), Shibani Sen Gupta, Subrata Sen, Tarun Chakravorty and Ujjwal Debnath.                  Event: An exhibition of paintings and sculptures When: Till April 5; 1 pm - 7.30 pm Where: Tejas Art Gallery, 11 Mayfair Road	                    
